description: A 59-year-old engineer, Neeraj Saxena, received permission from the Rajasthan High Court to visit his son in Singapore despite a pending departmental inquiry. The court emphasized that 'personal liberty' under Article 21 includes the right to travel abroad, with conditions on his timely return.
title: Rajasthan HC cites 'personal liberty', permits man under inquiry to travel abroad
Wikipedia's open-access editing 'dangerous': Delhi HC

description: Members of Bajrang Dal in Kanpur reported a Muslim man for wearing a 'Jai Shri Ram' T-shirt to conceal his identity while allegedly selling adulterated 'veg kebabs'. Police are considering action based on evidence. The issue arose when Bajrang Dal activists found the taste of the kebabs suspicious and called the authorities for investigation.
title: 'Shri Ram' T-shirt lands Muslim man in trouble

description: Three militants from Manipur's PREEPAK (PRO) and PLA were killed in a clash with Myanmar's rebel groups along the India-Myanmar border. Their bodies were retrieved and handed over to families, with hundreds attending the last rites in Manipur.
title: 3 Manipur rebels die in clash with Myanmar groups

description: Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang emphasizes India's potential to transform from an IT outsourcing hub into an AI innovation ecosystem, leveraging its vast data and computing expertise. With a significant portion of Nvidia's operations in India, Huang highlights the country's resources and stresses the importance of locally processing Indian data to maximize its value.
title: A third of Nvidia is here in India: CEO Jensen Huang

description: Protests erupted in Uttarkashi over claims of an illegal mosque, leading to clashes with police and charges against 200 individuals for various offenses. Eight officers were injured, prompting a thorough investigation. Local minorities expressed fear, while activists attribute rising communal tensions to political rhetoric.
title: Uttarkashi unrest: Over 200 charged with attempt to murder, rioting

description: Supreme Court dismissed CBI’s appeal challenging Bombay high court’s quashing of look out circulars against Rhea Chakraborty and her family in Sushant Singh Rajput’s death case. The apex court criticized the central probe agency for filing a frivolous appeal and emphasized that these circulars violated personal liberty without sufficient justification.
title: Relief for Rhea as SC bins ‘frivolous’ CBI plea against HC junking LOCs
Confusion in MVA as Congress neta declares new seat-sharing plan

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah’s wife, BM Parvathi, appeared before the Lokayukta police regarding the Mysore Urban Development Authority scam, providing information about a land transaction in Kesare gifted by her brother. Her low-profile visit comes a month after a special court's investigation order, with police recording details of the disputed land and compensation sites received from Muda.
title: Muda scam: Lokayukta cops quiz Siddaramaiah’s wife for 3 hours
Congress brass meets for over 2 hours; final candidate list expected today

description: A local court in Hathras has sentenced a man and his friend to life imprisonment for the 2015 murder of his mother. Investigation revealed the crime was an attempt to frame his rivals. His son, another conspirator, remains absconding.
title: UP man given life term for killing mom to frame rivals
Odisha governor seeking votes for daughter-in-law in Jharkhand
BJP: Priyanka Vadra affidavit silent on investment in Associated Journal Ltd
Security forces kill 2 Maoists after murder of Chandigarh villager
Bike thieves chase, gun down government officer in Bihar
EC officials, cops intercept gold jewellery worth Rs 138 crore
Madras HC seeks government view on waqf board-like body for church assets
Failure of government in Delhi, says Rahul

description: Edible oil prices have surged dramatically with palm oil up 37% and mustard oil 29% in the past month, impacting households and businesses during the festive season. The spike follows a government import duty hike and increasing global rates, leaving consumers to face high costs for upcoming months.
title: Edible oils costlier in festive season, palm oil price up 37% in a month
India, Germany to ink military logistics deal
27 flights, 3 hotels get bomb threats

description: NIA has offered a Rs 10 lakh reward for information leading to the capture of Anmol Bishnoi, a Canada-based criminal linked to actor Salman Khan's shooting incident and the murder of ex-NCP MLA Baba Siddique. Anmol, brother of jailed gangster Lawrence Bishnoi, is involved in narcotics, weapons smuggling, and extortion, managing operations from Canada. Both brothers face multiple charges.
title: Rs 10 lakh NIA reward for info on don Bishnoi’s Canada-based brother
Milind Deora to take on Aaditya Thackeray in high-voltage battle

description: Two anticyclones weakened Cyclone Dana's intensity, sparing Odisha from severe damage. The Bhitarkanika mangrove forest absorbed much of the storm's impact. Minimal casualties were reported, and effective measures ensured safety. Heavy rainfall and winds affected specific regions, with continued rains expected to subside by Saturday.
title: Two anticyclones, mangrove forest save Odisha from Cyclone Dana’s fury
It’s Zeeshan Siddique versus Varun Sardesai in Bandra East
NCP gives poll ticket to Sana Malik; Nawab unlikely to get nominated
Fadnavis couple income increases multifold in a decade

description: Vikash Yadav, implicated in a US murder-for-hire plot targeting separatist Gurpatwant Singh Pannun, is denied by his family and village in Pranpura, who assert he is a patriotic Indian government employee. The local community remains skeptical of US claims, defending Vikash's integrity.
title: Agent Vikash: Wanted by FBI, but patriot to his village
War cannot solve problems, says PM Modi as Scholz sounds alarm on Russia

description: In a tense Bigg Boss 18 episode, Muskan Bamne was evicted following housemates' votes, leaving Sara Khan and Tajinder Bagga to face jail time. Muskaan expressed gratitude for the opportunity and reflected on her journey influenced by Salman Khan, intensifying competition among remaining contestants.
title: Bigg Boss 18: Anupamaa fame Muskan Bamne gets eliminated

description: Ottawa denied the NIA’s request for Hardeep Singh Nijjar’s death certificate, citing queries about why India needed it. Nijjar, accused in nine cases, was murdered in 2022. This incident strained India-Canada relations, with mutual allegations and diplomatic actions ensuing.
title: Canada refuses NIA’s request for death certificate of Nijjar

description: AAP accused BJP 'goons' of attempting to attack Arvind Kejriwal during his padyatra in Vikaspuri, alleging BJP's frustration over Kejriwal's popularity and impending elections. BJP refuted the claims, attributing the incident to residents protesting against poor water supply. No complaint or evidence was reported to the police.
title: AAP: BJP ‘goons’ tried to attack Arvind Kejriwal; BJP denies

description: Germany will increase visas for skilled Indian workers from 20,000 to 90,000 annually, boosting its economic growth, as announced by PM Narendra Modi at the Asia-Pacific Conference of German Business. Additionally, Modi raised the issue of Ariha Shah, a three-year-old Indian girl in German foster care, with Chancellor Olaf Scholz closely following the case.
title: Germany ups visas for skilled Indian workers 4.5x to 90k

description: A Varanasi fast-track court has denied a plea for an additional invasive ASI survey of the Gyanvapi mosque complex. The petition sought excavation to verify claims of a temple below the mosque. The court stressed the need to adhere to Supreme Court orders protecting the structure.
title: Varanasi court rejects plea for excavation survey at Gyanvapi

description: Around 50% of troop disengagement at Depsang and Demchok in eastern Ladakh has been completed. The Indian Army plans to start coordinated patrolling with the PLA by month-end. Talks on buffer zones and other sensitive areas continue while both sides dismantle posts and monitor progress through UAVs.
title: Coordinated patrols by Army, PLA set to begin by October-end

description: Joe Rogan Podcast: Donald Trump is set to record an interview with Joe Rogan in Austin today though the episode's release date is unknown. Joe Rogan in 2022 called Donald Trump a threat to democracy, endorsed RFK Jr's candidacy for the presidential race over Donald Trump when Kennedy Jr was still an independent candidate, and also praised Kamala Harris' debate performance.
title: Donald Trump's Joe Rogan interview today: Time, past controversies

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 26, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Today's Horoscope: Astrological predictions for October 26, 2024

description: A terrorist ambush along the LoC near Gulmarg resulted in the deaths of four military personnel and two porters. Despite the attack, tourism in nearby Gulmarg remains unaffected. The military and local administration are responding intensely to locate the attackers.
title: Wounded soldier's death takes Gulmarg ambush toll to 5, biz as usual in tourist hub

description: With just 11 days left in the US election, the Democrats face a tight race despite initially appearing more secure. The gamble of replacing Joe Biden with Kamala Harris has led to a "dead heat" in the polls, with Harris struggling to win public approval. Despite significant campaign spending, poll leads have narrowed, and Republicans have gained traction on key issues like immigration. Additionally, traditional Democratic support among Muslim-Americans and Hispanic men has waned, with Trump gaining unexpected backing. The Democrats’ uphill battle is complicated by lingering voter scepticism and the challenge of overcoming the Republican edge in swing states.
title: US Election Top 10: Why Democrats have reason to worry

description: WWE is reportedly planning high-profile bouts for Saturday Night’s Main Event on December 14, featuring Cody Rhodes versus Kevin Owens and Gunther versus Damian Priest. These anticipated matchups are creating excitement among fans, though they remain unconfirmed. The potential showdowns could mark significant moments for Rhodes and Priest, adding intrigue for WWE's future events.
title: Potential blockbuster matches set for WWE Saturday night’s main event

description: Maurizio Cattelan's provocative art piece 'Comedian', a banana duct-taped to a wall, will be auctioned by Sotheby's in New York City. The buyer receives a certificate of authenticity and instructions, not the original banana. The artwork, which evoked intense debates since its 2019 debut, could fetch $1.5 million.
title: Art goes 'Banana': 'Comedian' painting could fetch $1.5 million
'Because he’s a mensch': Holocaust survivor slams Kamala for comparing Trump to Hitler

description: Germany increases annual visas for skilled Indian workers from 20,000 to 90,000, enhancing bilateral ties. Chancellor Scholz and PM Modi focus on economic growth, defence, and clean energy collaboration. A new green hydrogen roadmap and streamlined visa process are also introduced, marking deeper cooperation.
title: Germany to increase annual visas for skilled Indian workers to 90,000

description: Afghanistan A triumphed over India A by 20 runs in an Emerging Teams Asia Cup T20 semi-final. Despite Ramandeep Singh's fighting half-century, India A fell short, ending at 186/7. Sediqullah Atal and Zubaid Akbari starred for Afghanistan, posting a strong 206/4. Afghanistan A face Sri Lanka A in the final on Sunday.
title: Emerging Teams Asia Cup: Afghanistan A power past India A

description: India's 18-member Test squad for the series against Australia, starting November 22, is led by Rohit Sharma. Notable absences include Mohammed Shami and Kuldeep Yadav, while reserves Mukesh Kumar, Navdeep Saini, and Khaleel Ahmed are named. The series will feature five Test matches.
title: India squad for BGT: No Shami, Axar

description: In campaign speeches, Trump criticizes the Biden-Harris administration's border policies, calling America a "garbage can" due to illegal immigration. He uses harsh language against immigrants and political rivals, and forebodes a civil war, citing increasing societal tensions and the risk of violent clashes post-election.
title: America the Beautiful has become a 'garbage can' for the world: Trump

description: ​Earlier it was reported that the paper was dragging its feet on the decision as owner Jeff Bezos is not willing to endorse Kamala Harris alienating Donald Trump. The decision to not endorse anyone confirms the dithering. A New York Post report earlier said that the editorial board of the Washington Post wrote its endorsement of Kamala Harris but received no approval from Bezos or Will Lewis to publish it.
title: Washington Post won't endorse Trump or Harris this election -- first time in 36 years

description: Glenn Maxwell disclosed details of team infighting with mentor Virender Sehwag during his time at Kings XI Punjab in the IPL. Maxwell discussed the deteriorating relationship and power struggles that impacted team decisions and performance. This friction ultimately led to a strained relationship and his departure from the team.
title: Maxwell makes startling revelation about his rift with Sehwag
Two Chennai school students hospitalised after 'gas leak'

description: Bryan Johnson, a 47-year-old tech millionaire, reveals his successful battle against male pattern baldness and premature greying by sharing his multi-step method. Bryan Johnson's transformation story is more than just a tale of reversing hair loss—it’s a testament to the power of taking a proactive and multi-faceted approach. His journey shows that it’s possible to maintain a youthful appearance and lush hair well into middle age.
title: Millionaire Bryan Johnson on how he hacked baldness, hair greying
3,500 children, 30 countries: UK catfishing predator jailed for life

description: Ukraine's bid to blacklist Russia over high-risk money laundering was rejected by India, China, Saudi Arabia, and South Africa during the FATF discussions in Paris. Brazil also opposed the proposal, which led to a delay for further evidence gathering. Russia's FATF membership remains suspended.
title: India, China reject Ukraine's bid to add Russia to FATF's 'black list'
'Endorse 5 names or ...': Maha SP chief Abu Azmi warns MVA, slams Cong

description: Income disparity among those earning up to Rs 5 lakh annually has declined by over 74.2% between FY 2013-14 and 2022-23, as per an SBI report. This improvement highlights the government's efforts in boosting lower-income groups' earnings. The report also mentions a shift towards progressive taxation and improved tax compliance.
title: Income disparity declined 74.2% in last 10 years: SBI Study

description: Former India coach Ravi Shastri criticized Rohit Sharma's defensive captaincy on Day 2 of the second Test against New Zealand in Pune. Shastri emphasized the need for an attacking field to bowl out New Zealand for 120. New Zealand, poised for a historic series win in India, led by 301 runs at stumps in their second innings.
title: Shastri fumes over Rohit's defensive captaincy on Day 2

description: A Varanasi court denied the Hindu side's request for a fresh ASI survey of the Gyanvapi premises. Advocate Rastogi plans to appeal in the high court within 30 days, arguing that the initial survey did not meet court-specified requirements, particularly regarding team composition and survey areas.
title: Gyanvapi case: Varanasi court dismisses plea for additional ASI survey
'Kuch nahi bachta hai': Rahul visits barber for a trim and his story

description: Indian High Commissioner to Canada, Sanjay Kumar Verma, describes a close encounter with Khalistani activists wielding swords in Alberta. Verma said, "I am not an expert on Canadian law about open carrying so I will not be able to say that. But most likely they would have said that it was 'kirpan' which is a small blade whereas they had swords in their hand."
title: 'Swords in hand': Envoy Verma recounts attack bid by Khalistanis in Canada

description: Mukesh Ambani applauds wife Nita Ambani as the driving force behind the Jio World Centre during a chat with Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang in Mumbai.
title: When Mukesh Ambani told Nvidia CEO that Nita 'instructed' him to say that

description: India facing a significant challenge as they trail by 301 runs after New Zealand's strong performance on day two of the second Test. Mitchell Santner's exceptional 7/53 dismantled India's batting lineup, while Tom Latham's 86 further solidified New Zealand's commanding position.
title: 2nd Test: Five talking points from Day 2 as India batters surrender again

description: King Charles III hosted an official dinner for Commonwealth leaders at CHOGM 2024 in Apia, Samoa. He addressed historical injustices and their current impact. During his tour, he participated in a kava-drinking ceremony, symbolizing Samoan tradition and cultural respect.
title: In pic: When Kiren Rijiju met King Charles III

description: Shiv Sena leader Milind Deora hints at a head-to-head contest with Aaditya Thackeray for the Worli assembly seat, emphasizing overdue justice for Worli residents. Former Congress MP Deora, now with Sena, aims for the seat, while Thackeray has already submitted his nomination. Both camps are actively campaigning and strategizing for the high-stakes election.
title: 'It’s Worli now': Milind Deora's big hint on fight against Aaditya
'LAC patrolling to resume after India, China pull back troops to 2020 positions'

description: China has launched a diplomatic push to improve relations with US allies and partners amid economic challenges and possible instability from a Trump presidency. Efforts include a breakthrough with India and ongoing talks with Japan. Beijing seeks to buffer economic troubles and find allies amidst potential US trade threats, while remaining firm on core issues.
title: Why China is playing nice with India, other US allies

description: Actress Rhea Chakraborty who has been in the spotlight for the Sushant Singh Rajput death case, has a reason to feel relieved. On Friday, the Supreme Court dismissed the petitions filed by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI), the State of Maharashtra, and the Bureau of Immigration, which sought to challenge the Bombay High Court's decision to quash Look-out Circulars (LOCs) against her.
title: Sushant Singh death: SC rejects CBI plea against Rhea Chakraborty

description: Miami Dolphins quarterback Tua Tagovailoa's multiple concussions reignite concerns about long-term effects of head injuries in the NFL. Jason Kelce calls for increased research on concussion impacts and improved safety protocols. Despite a noted decline in preseason concussion rates, experts emphasize the need for more comprehensive studies to protect players' health.
title: Jason Kelce says that NFL should prioritize research on long-term concussion effects

description: A one-hour video exposing a 'digital arrest' scam shows a journalist's experience with fraudsters posing as police, using false accusations, fake documents, and intimidation tactics to manipulate victims into transferring money. The video serves as a crucial warning for public vigilance against such online scams.
title: Digital arrest shows how scammers use fake Aadhaar, Police uniform & more

description: Over 25 aircrafts received bomb threats on Friday afternoon, including over seven IndiGo flights. Authorities are taking necessary precautions and working closely with relevant agencies to ensure safety. The government has requested data from Meta and X to track down the individuals behind these threats. Customers are advised to stay calm and cooperate with security protocols.
title: Over 25 flights received bomb threats on Friday: Report

description: A political dispute flared up between the BJP and the Congress over claims about Congress president Kharge’s treatment at Priyanka Gandhi Vadra’s nomination filing in Wayanad. Congress leader Venugopal replied to BJP allegations, confirming Kharge’s presence and accusing the BJP of spreading misinformation. Meanwhile, BJP representatives criticized Congress for allegedly disrespecting Kharge, a senior Dalit leader.
title: Was Kharge made to wait outside during Priyanka's nomination? Cong clarifies

description: New Zealand's captain Tom Latham scored a crucial half-century, extending their lead over India to more than 200 runs on Day 2 of the second Test in Pune. India's batsmen struggled in their first innings, raising concerns as they face a daunting task to win this Test and level the series against a dominant New Zealand.
title: Is it game over for India already? History puts Rohit & Co. on the backfoot

description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee announced one fatality and the evacuation of 2.16 lakh residents due to Cyclone Dana. Severe damage has occurred in several districts, particularly affecting kaccha houses. Relief efforts are underway, and weather reports indicate heavy rainfall in coastal Odisha and south Gangetic West Bengal. Air services have been restored.
title: Cyclone Dana: One dead in West Bengal, says CM Mamata

description: Rohit Sharma admitted misreading the pitch as India fell to 46 runs on Day 1 of the Bengaluru Test, their lowest home total. The lack of intent and adaptation from the batters led to another poor performance against spin in the subsequent Pune Test, prompting urgent improvement before their Australia tour.
title: Blame the batters, not the pitch, as India collapse again

description: Reliance Jio announces its True 5G Diwali Dhamaka offer with benefits worth up to Rs 3,350 with vouchers from EaseMyTrip, Ajio, and Swiggy.
title: Jio Diwali Dhamaka offers free Swiggy, Ajio vouchers with these plans

description: The Delhi Police's special cell apprehended seven shooters linked to the Lawrence Bishnoi gang from various locales in Punjab and neighboring states. Lawrence Bishnoi, imprisoned in Sabarmati, is a primary suspect in Sidhu Moose Wala's murder case. The NIA offered Rs 10 lakh for tips on his brother Anmol, wanted for a shooting near Salman Khan's Mumbai home.
title: Delhi Police arrests 7 shooters of Lawrence Bishnoi gang

description: Lt Gen. MV Suchindra Kumar of the Indian Army's Northern Command stated that the Army is reassessing strategies following the Baramulla terrorist attack and suspected cross-border support. Emphasising integration of military and social outreach, the Army also aims to empower youth, promote education and sports, and foster a peaceful environment in Jammu & Kashmir.
title: 'Support from across border': Northern Army Commander on J&K attack
'India, China military disengagement in Depsang & Demchok by Oct 28-29'

description: India was dismissed for 156 in their first innings of the second Test against New Zealand, giving the visitors a 103-run lead. Despite Washington Sundar's 7/59, India's batting collapsed with only Ravindra Jadeja offering some resistance. New Zealand's Mitchell Santner took 7/53, making India's challenge to stay competitive in the match and series harder.
title: First time in 23 years! India register an unwanted feat in home Tests

description: Farooq Abdullah said that ongoing violence in Jammu and Kashmir will persist until India and Pakistan improve relations. Referring to a recent ambush in Gulmarg, he urged Pakistan to seek friendship with India and focus on its own issues. He also called for the Centre to grant full statehood to Jammu and Kashmir.
title: 'Witnessing it for last 30 yrs': Farooq Abdullah calls out Pakistan

description: Around 25 women from Lendra panchayat, Bastar, walked over 25km to Jagdalpur to demand toilets, water, an anganwadi center, and nurse facilities. Despite the area being declared open-defecation-free in 2015-16, married women live in new homes without toilets. Facing daily hardships, they have warned of protests if their demands are not met.
title: Toilet, not a 'prem katha' for these women in Bastar

description: India, typically dominant on home spinning tracks, struggled as Mitchell Santner's spin led to their batting collapse against New Zealand. This pattern of faltering on their own spin-friendly pitches has been previously observed against Australia in Indore 2023, and England in Hyderabad 2024 and Chennai 2021. Let's have a look at some of the previous instances.
title: Team India's struggles against spin bowlers

description: Rahul Gandhi criticized the NDA government for its failure to ensure security in Jammu and Kashmir, highlighting the rising terrorist activities and targeted killings. Following a recent attack that resulted in the deaths of soldiers and porters, he demanded immediate accountability and actions to restore peace and safety in the region.
title: J&K terror attack: Rahul slams Centre's 'failed policies' for lapses

description: Virat Kohli struggled with spin bowling once again during the second Test against New Zealand in Pune, getting bowled by Mitchell Santner for just 1 run. This marked his 21st dismissal to spin in Asia since 2021. Kohli's inconsistency against spinners has placed India in a tough spot, with the hosts already trailing New Zealand 0-1 in the series.
title: 21 dismissals in 26 innings: Kohli's struggles against spin in Asia continue

description: Telecom companies have warned of possible disruptions in online transactions starting November 1, due to a new TRAI rule on message traceability. They have sought additional time for proper implementation to avoid blocking important messages like OTPs.
title: Why your OTP for online purchases may not come from November

description: On October 25, Google honored legendary playback singer KK (Krishnakumar Kunnath) with a special Doodle, marking his debut with "Chhod Aaye Hum" from Maachis in 1996. Over his three-decade career, he recorded over 500 Hindi songs, 3,500 jingles, and numerous tracks in regional languages, leaving an indelible legacy.
title: Google honors singer KK with special doodle on anniversary of his debut

description: In 2005, Intel's decision to forgo acquiring Nvidia for $20 billion resulted in missed opportunities, as Nvidia now dominates the AI chip market. Despite Intel's internal efforts and acquisitions to compete, they lag significantly behind Nvidia, with current CEO Gelsinger acknowledging the company's challenges in catching up.
title: When Intel ‘decided’ Nvidia is not worth spending $20 billion on

description: Virat Kohli experienced disappointment after being bowled out for 1 by a full toss from New Zealand's Mitchell Santner in the second Pune Test. Former cricketer Sanjay Manjrekar labeled Kohli’s shot as the worst of his career. Santner took 7 wickets for 53 runs, leading to India's collapse at 156 runs.
title: 'Worst shot': Ex-cricketer criticises Virat's dismissal

description: Chief Justice of India, DY Chandrachud, reminisces about his days as an All India Radio presenter, sharing how he was captivated by iconic news voices and ultimately became a presenter himself. He fondly recalls auditioning in Delhi and hosting both Hindi and English programs.
title: 'I remember my first programme': CJI Chandrachud looks back at his AIR host days

description: NASA's Crew-8 mission has concluded after 236 days in space, as the team successfully splashed down off Pensacola, Florida, in a SpaceX Dragon spacecraft. The mission covered 100 million miles and involved eight spacecraft arrivals and departures at the ISS, underscoring ongoing space station operations.
title: Watch: Nasa's SpaceX Dragon spacecraft returns to Earth after 236 days in space

description: BJP's Shehzad Poonawala condemned AAP for not addressing Delhi's internal pollution issues, highlighting CJI Chandrachud's halting of morning walks due to poor air quality. Delhi’s AQI reached hazardous levels, with readings like 288 at Jhilmil Industrial area. Poonawala emphasized that citizens are suffering and criticized AAP's ongoing blame game.
title: 'AAP can even blame Israel, Lebanon for pollution': Shehzad Poonawala

description: Shiv Sena faction under Maharashtra Chief Minister Eknath Shinde aims to field Milind Deora in Worli against Aaditya Thackeray and Sandeep Deshpande. Aaditya Thackeray is confident about his victory, supported by Shiv Sena (UBT) leaders. Both Mahayuti and Maha Vikas Aghadi alliances are gearing up for the Maharashtra Assembly elections scheduled on November 20.
title: Shiv Sena might field Milind Deora against ​​Aaditya Thackeray from Worli

description: With rising air pollution, the government has urged states to enhance healthcare readiness for the festive and winter seasons. Measures include discouraging stubble burning, limiting firecrackers, and promoting public transport. Vulnerable groups should minimize outdoor activities and use cleaner fuels. Public awareness campaigns and monitoring air quality are also emphasized.
title: 'Minimise exposure, use public transport': Centre's advisory on rising pollution

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal made history as the first Indian batter to score 1,000 Test runs in a calendar year before turning 23. Achieved during the second Test against New Zealand, Jaiswal's 30 runs contributed to this milestone. Despite his achievement, India faced struggles at 70/4 against New Zealand's first-innings total of 259.
title: Big Record! Jaiswal becomes first Indian to achieve historic feat

description: Virat Kohli's lively on-field behavior shines during India's second Test against New Zealand. A friendly exchange between Kohli and Tim Southee caught fans' attention. India, trailing 0-1 in the series, dismissed New Zealand for 259 in Pune. Kohli's performance will be key against Australia in the Border Gavaskar Trophy starting November 22. In the opening Test, which New Zealand won by eight wickets in Bengaluru, Kohli scored an impressive 70 runs.
title: Virat Kohli-Tim Southee bromance steals show

description: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz has arrived in New Delhi for a three-day official visit to India, where he will join Prime Minister Narendra Modi for comprehensive talks on enhancing strategic ties in defence, trade, and clean energy. They will co-chair the 7th Intergovernmental Consultations, a platform for ministerial discussions across various sectors.
title: German Chancellor Olaf Scholz meets PM Modi in Delhi

description: After a 35-year legal battle, Gujarat High Court approved the Rs 82 crore sale of 58,000 square yards of Aryoday Spinning & Weaving Mills land in Ahmedabad. Devbhoomi Agrifresh Pvt Ltd won the bid amid raised objections. Only Rs 55 lakh has been disbursed to the mill's workers since 1989, with 60% deceased.
title: Bankrupt Gujarat mill's land sold after 35yrs, but 60% of workers died waiting for dues

description: Annu Kapoor says that the makers changed the name of the lead character in the movie 'Chak De! India' to portray Muslim as a good character. He further added that they make fun of a pandit here. The actor said that the film based based on Mir Ranjan Negi and not Kabir Khan.
title: Annu Kapoor alleges that facts were changed in Shah Rukh Khan's 'Chak De! India'

description: In an unprecedented operation, Kerala's GST intelligence wing seized 108 kg of unaccounted gold from 78 jewellery units in Thrissur. The covert raids revealed concealed sales turnover up to Rs 1,200 crore. The gold, now in the treasury, can be reclaimed post payment of penalties and GST. Investigations will continue over weeks or months.
title: In commando-style operation, 108kg of unaccounted gold seized in Kerala

description: Gursimran Kaur, a 19-year-old Indian girl, was tragically found dead inside a walk-in oven at a Walmart bakery in Canada. Her mother discovered her body after failing to locate her for an hour. Authorities have launched an investigation, while the community has raised over $130,000 for the family's support.
title: Who was Gursimran Kaur? Walmart employee found dead in walk-in oven

description: Tasmania sensationally restricted reigning champions Western Australia to a shocking 53 runs in their Domestic One-Day Cup match, with spinner Beau Webster grabbing 6 wickets and pacer Billy Stanlake taking 3. WA collapsed dramatically, losing eight wickets for just one wide, crumbling from 52/2.
title: 8 wickets for 1 run! Dramatic batting collapse in Perth

description: India makes significant changes after the first Test defeat, introducing Shubman Gill, Akash Deep, and Washington Sundar. Ravichandran Ashwin's crucial wickets aid India as New Zealand reaches 92-2 at lunch on the first day. Washington Sundar's seven wickets help dismiss New Zealand for 259 runs.
title: Watch: 'Rohit bhai, bharosa rakho... ' How Sarfaraz convinced Rohit

description: Virat Kohli was dismissed by Mitchell Santner in a surprising manner, missing a full toss that crashed into his stumps during the second Test against New Zealand in Pune. Kohli’s unexpected dismissal left him frustrated, particularly after scoring 0 and 70 in the previous Test in Bengaluru. Kohli had come to the crease after Shubman Gill’s dismissal to Santner.
title: Virat Kohli misjudges full toss, walks back fuming

description: Ten police officers were killed and seven injured in a militant attack on a Frontier Constabulary post near Pakistan's Afghan border. The Pakistan Taliban claimed responsibility for the assault in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. The region has seen increased militancy since the Afghan Taliban's return to power in 2021, with frequent attacks targeting security forces.
title: 10 Pakistan cops shot dead by Taliban at check post near Afghan border

description: Indonesia has banned the iPhone 16 due to Apple's unfulfilled investment commitments. The device is illegal without IMEI certification and cannot be sold or operated in the country. Apple's pending investments and TKDN certification requirements must be met before sales permits are issued.
title: Indonesia bans iPhone 16: 'The device is illegal, report it to us' says minister

description: Three hotels in Tirupati received bomb threats through email, leading to an investigation by the local police. Circle Inspector Srinivasulu confirmed that an FIR has been filed, and efforts are underway to identify the culprits. The police are examining various leads and promise swift action against those responsible for the threatening emails.
title: Three hotels in Tirupati receive bomb threat

description: At a rally with Donald Trump, Vivek Ramaswamy proposed single-day nationwide voting with paper ballots and government ID. He urged Republicans to participate in early voting to secure a win, comparing the 2024 election to the American Revolution and Trump to George Washington.
title: 'Play by the rules': Why Ramaswamy is pushing for single-day nationwide voting

description: Virat Kohli's lively on-field personality shone during the first Test against New Zealand, delighting fans with his humorous mimicry. Despite his solid 70-run effort, India lost the match by eight wickets. Kohli’s form will be crucial for India in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Australia. The Border Gavaskar Trophy starts November 22.
title: Mimicking Shubman Gill? Virat Kohli leave fans in splits

description: The National Investigation Agency announced a Rs 10 lakh bounty for Anmol Bishnoi, brother of jailed gangster Lawrence Bishnoi. Anmol is linked to Baba Siddique's murder and 18 other criminal cases. He allegedly communicated with assassins through a messaging app and posted a warning to Salman Khan. Mumbai Police issued a lookout circular for him in April.
title: NIA announces bounty of Rs 10 lakh on Lawrence Bishnoi's brother

description: Rohit Sharma faced criticism after India replaced Kuldeep Yadav with Washington Sundar for the second Test against New Zealand. Sundar justified the decision by taking career-best figures of 7-59, complementing Ashwin and Jadeja, and expressed his joy at being part of the spin attack. Washington emphasized the significance of his return to the Test squad and his performance in the match.
title: Gambhir's priceless reaction to Sundar's magic moment

description: Violence erupted in Dehradun as right-wing groups and locals clashed with police over access to a mosque, leading to injuries and attacks on Muslim-owned shops. Despite the mosque's confirmed legality, protesters accused it of being illegal and demanded its demolition, escalating tensions.
title: 4 cops hurt as violence erupts at anti-mosque rally in Uttarkashi

description: Delhi continues to face severe air pollution with the AQI recorded at 354 on Friday morning, indicating 'very poor' air. The situation is expected to remain dire over the weekend, with calm winds and low temperatures hindering pollutant dispersion.
title: Delhi's air still in very poor zone with AQI at 389; may turn severe

description: October 25th, 2024, presents unique challenges and opportunities for individuals governed by different numerology numbers. From introspection and spiritual exploration to relationship harmony and professional frustrations, each number faces specific influences. Emphasis is on inner strength, balance, strategic planning, and emotional well-being to navigate the day effectively.
title: Numerology predictions today: Read your personalised forecast

description: Salman Khan faces renewed threats linked to the 1998 blackbuck case. After politician Baba Siddique's death, Salman and his father received ominous messages. Salman's father denies his son's guilt, while discussions on resolving the conflict vary from apologies to alleged financial offers. Increased security measures are in place as Salman prepares for an international tour.
title: Salman Khan-Bishnoi feud: How it started and where it stands right now

description: Washington Sundar played a crucial role in India's second Test match after their defeat in Bengaluru. He showcased an impressive bowling spell, taking 7 wickets for 59 runs, and gave India's campaign a significant uplift. Sundar credited his Ranji Trophy experience for his performance and expressed gratitude to the team management and selectors.
title: Washington Sundar adds dash of magic to team's plans

description: Jason Gillespie urges former cricketers to stop undue criticism of Pakistan's national team, as it impacts player morale. He highlights the importance of positive feedback from past idols and expresses frustration over his limited role in team decisions, advocating for improved communication. Gillespie also expressed frustration over his reduced role. The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) removed him and Test captain Shan Masood from the selection committee and took away their input on pitch preparation.
title: 'Former players are paid ... ': Pakistan coach

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella's compensation rose 63% to $79.1 million in fiscal 2024, driven by increased stock awards as Microsoft’s market value surpassed $3 trillion. Nadella’s stock awards jumped from $39 million to $71 million. Despite strong performance, Nadella reduced his cash incentive due to reported cybersecurity breaches. Comparatively, Apple CEO Tim Cook earned $63.2 million in 2023.
title: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella sees 63% rise in compensation to $79.1 million

description: Pune police are targeting youngsters idolizing gangster Lawrence Bishnoi on social media, leading to extortion threats. These youths, often from poor families, are swayed by glamorized criminal culture. Authorities are counseling them to prevent crime inclination. Experts highlight the societal neglect and media glorification as factors driving this dangerous trend.
title: Bishnoi’s ‘admirers’ under cop lens, ‘some using gangster name to threaten’

description: Legendary David Warner's lifetime ban from leadership roles in Australian cricket has been lifted following his respectful appeal. The decision came after a three-person panel assessed his contrite presentation, enabling Warner to pursue leadership positions, including with Sydney Thunder in the Big Bash League. Warner was a central figure in the 2018 "Sandpaper-gate" incident.
title: Warner's ban lifted 6 years after ball-tampering scandal

description: A 26-year-old man, Mohit, along with two friends, was arrested for murdering his mother, Sangeeta Tyagi, after she refused to give him Rs 20,000 for repairing his music system. Mohit and his friends lured Sangeeta to a deserted location and killed her by smashing her face with a brick. All three have been booked for murder.
title: Mother refuses to pay Rs 20,000 for speakers, son smashes her face with brick

description: In Pakistan, traditional marriage matchmaking by rishta aunties faces disruption from Muslim-specific marriage apps like Muzz, which have gained significant popularity. These digital platforms, offering halal features, challenge the conventional arranged marriage system but still retain the importance of family involvement in the process.
title: Marriage apps in Pakistan, where dating is banned, is taking over 'Rishta Aunties' job

description: Police revealed that the masterminds behind NCP politician Baba Siddique's murder promised a fake passport for shooter Gurmail Singh and paid him Rs 50,000 for his role. Zeeshan Siddique's statement was recorded, and authorities arrested 14 individuals while searching for three main suspects.
title: Baba Siddique murder: One shooter promised fake passport to flee

description: Siemens AG is considering acquiring Altair Engineering Inc, a leading engineering software provider valued at $9.1 billion. This move aligns with Siemens' strategic shift towards software-driven product lines. Both companies have declined to comment, and the acquisition is not yet guaranteed as other bidders may emerge.
title: German giant Siemens may make its biggest-ever acquisition with US software giant

description: At Nvidia's AI Summit in Mumbai, Bollywood actor Akshay Kumar and Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang bonded over martial arts. Huang received a warm welcome, emphasizing India's strength in IT. Nvidia plans to supply AI chips to Indian companies, with a notable partnership with Reliance Industries, aiming to transform India into a global AI leader.
title: Bollywood superstar Akshay Kumar met Nvidia CEO: Now I know why Nvidia is ...
